article.description: Dylan Frye had a career-high 30 points as Bowling Green beat Dartmouth 76-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Frye scores 30 to lift Bowling Green past Dartmouth 76-69
article.linkText: Frye scores 30 to lift Bowling Green past Dartmouth 76-69
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Dylan Frye had a career-high 30 points as Bowling Green beat Dartmouth 76-69 on Saturday. Trey Diggs had 17 points and seven rebounds for Bowling Green (6-2). Marlon Sierra added 11 points. Daeqwon Plowden had 8 points and 12 rebounds for the hosts. Aaryn Rai had 20 points and eight rebounds for the Big Green (5-2). Taurus Samuels added 15 points. James Foye had 13 points. Bowling Green plays Oakland at home next Saturday. Dartmouth plays Georgia State on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
